= Tahini

This Substance is useful for Hummus. Supposedly sometimes people eat it on its
own, or use it in other things; not that I would know.

== Equipment

- Oven
- Baking sheet
- Food processor#Fn.food-processor

== Ingredients

// TODO: metric
- 1 cup sesame seeds
- 1/4 cup olive oil, minimum

Yields enough for five batches of @spicy-hummus.

== Steps
// TODO: retry this recipe
+ Preheat oven to 175°C (350°F).
+ Spread sesame seeds onto baking sheet.
+ Place baking sheet in oven & stir occasionally#footnote[~TO-DO: figure out if this stirring is necessary] for 10-12 minutes.
+ Blend seeds with olive oil.
  - If the resulting substance is not smoothing out properly, add a little more oil.

== Trivia

If it's not obvious enough, the only reason I have this recipe in here is to make @spicy-hummus. Couldn't be bothered to buy tahini, but I did already have sesame seeds at home.
